Package io.pivotal.rti.protocols

protocols-sdk API package.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ProtocolAdapter
    Protocol Adapter API contract in protocols SDK.
    ProtocolMetricManager  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractProtocolAdapter
    Default implementation for protocols SDK contract ProtocolAdapter Implementers of new protocol adapters are encouraged to extend this class and override the abstract methods in it, primarily AbstractProtocolAdapter.bytesToProtocolEvent(byte[]) In addition to implement the SDK contract, this class also provides hooks into JMX metrics and other error handling.
    ProtocolAttributeMap  
    ProtocolDetailMap
    Custom implementation of Map that allows to store protocol specific details.
    ProtocolEvent
    Core domain class provided through the codecs API and needed for implementing a valid ProtocolAdapter.
    ProtocolEventDefaults  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ConstructorArgumentKeys
    If the ProtocolAdapter implementation has constructor parameters and if the Spring auto-configuration mechanism is not used, then you must tag your constructor with ConstructorArgumentKeys annotation and provide keys that correspond to the parameters in the declaration order.
    ProtocolDetail
    Annotation to let RTI discover new fields contributed through ProtocolAdapter implementations.
    ProtocolDetails
    Annotation to let RTI discover new fields contributed through ProtocolAdapter implementations.
    TextProtocol
    In order to implement a text based protocol adapter, the ProtocolAdapter must be annotated with TextProtocol.
